g.text: 1. inline CSS - style attribute in HTML
margin collapse only works with top and bottom margin
- padding : 5 px - sets 5px padding on all 4 sides
- padding : 5 px 10px - sets 5px padding on top and bottom, 10 px on left and right padding: y x
- padding 1px 2px 3px 4px - 1px top, 2px -right, 3px - bottom , 4px - left, works in clockwise starting from top
the selector which is more specific is going to be applied
I(C/A)E - ID Class/Attribute Element 3 digit number
div>span - select span which are direct children of div
general - elem1 ~ elem2 (selects all elem2 which is sibling of elem 1)
adjacent- elem1+elem2 ((selects only elem2 which is adjacent sibling of elem 1))
specify link pesudo class in this order only

::after p::after Insert something after the content of each

element

::before p::before Insert something before the content of each

element

::first-letter p::first-letter Selects the first letter of each

element

::first-line p::first-line Selects the first line of each

element
::marker ::marker Selects the markers of list items
::selection p::selection Selects the portion of an element that is selected by a user
p ~ span targets span 2,3 (always select the right sibling)
